President Biden held separate calls with Mayor Jane Castor of Tampa, Mayor Ken Welch of St. Petersburg, and Mayor Frank Hibbard of Clearwater to discuss preparations for the potential impacts of Hurricane Ian. The President spoke about the ongoing efforts of federal, state, and local governments to pre-position resources and initiate evacuation operations. He directed FEMA Administrator Criswell to ensure that all available federal support is surged to prepare in advance and respond after the storm. President Biden emphasized the importance of families heeding evacuation orders.